Çalık Enerji
Çalik Enerji is a Turkish energy company of the Çalık Holding, which was established in 1998. The main areas of operations include:
Çalik Enerji has oil and gas exploration and production activities in Turkey, Iraq, Afghanistan, Azerbaijan, and Turkmenistan (notably in the Ýolöten Gas Field). It constructs together with Italian company Eni the Samsun-Ceyhan Pipeline to transport crude oil from the Black Sea to Mediterranean Sea. It also operates power plants in Turkey and Turkmenistan. 
